    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "For private network if there are no contracts, it is just overhead that requires some memory, start-up time and CPU usage.\r\n\r\nI perfectly understand that for mainnet it is highly undesirable when specific node could opt-out of executing EVM code. But in context of private network it may be just distraction (I cannot think yet of a case when it is undesirable )\r\n\r\nAnyways, I thought to raise a ticket, to see if more people would be interested and could vote such option.\r\n\r\nAlso before there were other than Solidity languages, hopefully will be others.",
